WEBVTT

00:08.508 --> 00:10.910
♪♪♪

00:55.288 --> 00:56.689
PEDRO: I wasn't even planning
to leave so early,

00:56.756 --> 00:59.959
but I couldn't sleep, and just
as I was untying the boat,

01:00.026 --> 01:02.595
I heard something
hitting the hull.

01:07.467 --> 01:08.234
[Malena laughing]

01:13.406 --> 01:14.441
PAULA: Girls, listen up.

01:14.507 --> 01:15.575
If I ever find you
hitchhiking again,

01:15.642 --> 01:17.710
I'm gonna lock you up
for three days.

01:17.811 --> 01:18.878
- And I mean it, girls.
- We know.

01:18.945 --> 01:20.447
EVA: Fine.
- Hey, there are lots of psychos

01:20.513 --> 01:21.915
- out there.
- Okay.

01:22.015 --> 01:23.249
- Be careful.
- Costa, you're a party-pooper.

01:23.316 --> 01:25.852
EVA: Thank you very much.
SANDRA: Thank you, Costa.

01:25.919 --> 01:27.687
Bye girls.
Have lots of fun.

01:29.055 --> 01:30.690
- We love you.
ALL: Mwah!

01:30.757 --> 01:32.959
- Bye.
- Thank you.

01:33.026 --> 01:34.227
PEDRO: I didn't know
who else to call,

01:34.327 --> 01:35.929
and I remembered
you lived nearby.

01:38.131 --> 01:40.433
You did the right thing, Pedro.

01:40.533 --> 01:42.368
And now, go call the station
and tell my dad

01:42.435 --> 01:44.571
Malena Baldo
has been found dead, okay?

01:46.172 --> 01:47.173
[sighs]

02:34.754 --> 02:36.990
DOLORES: Where is Zhou?

02:39.292 --> 02:42.962
All right.
We can get started without him.

02:44.397 --> 02:45.632
It's not a problem.

02:53.239 --> 02:55.508
[Marta screaming]

03:02.882 --> 03:05.084
[screaming continues]

03:05.151 --> 03:07.053
♪♪♪

03:37.717 --> 03:40.486
WOMAN: How are you
feeling? Better?

03:44.090 --> 03:46.759
You fainted
and came in very dehydrated.

03:49.162 --> 03:50.430
[wincing]

03:50.530 --> 03:53.399
Do you remember what happened?

03:53.466 --> 03:54.067
How long have I been here?

03:56.803 --> 03:58.905
- I've got to go.
- No, no.

03:59.005 --> 04:02.408
For now, all you have to do
is rest.

04:02.475 --> 04:04.744
Do you want me
to call someone?

04:04.844 --> 04:06.346
The doctor will be
right with you.

04:19.525 --> 04:20.093
[door closes]

04:22.829 --> 04:24.264
[grunts]

04:39.045 --> 04:40.480
[elevator dings]

04:44.384 --> 04:46.753
[clattering]

04:49.389 --> 04:49.956
[door closes]

05:09.042 --> 05:10.476
[elevator dings]

05:14.113 --> 05:16.516
[elevator door opening]

05:18.718 --> 05:20.753
We have to get out.

05:20.853 --> 05:23.723
We have to get
out of here.

05:23.790 --> 05:26.292
We have to.
We have to get out of here.

05:28.161 --> 05:29.962
We have to get out.

05:30.029 --> 05:33.599
We have to.
We have to get out.

05:33.666 --> 05:35.568
We have to get out of here.

05:44.610 --> 05:45.945
[high-pitch ringing]

05:47.714 --> 05:50.049
[people chattering]

05:56.823 --> 05:58.191
REPORTER: Hurry!

06:02.495 --> 06:04.831
[chattering continues]

06:11.237 --> 06:12.705
RAMON: Hey, hey, listen, please.
REPORTER: Sir,

06:12.805 --> 06:13.973
who found the bodies
this morning?

06:14.040 --> 06:15.608
It's still too soon
to jump to conclusions.

06:15.675 --> 06:16.876
We're doing everything
within our power

06:16.943 --> 06:19.145
and we've already started
the search operation.

06:19.245 --> 06:22.515
Please, stay behind the cars,
that'll be all.

06:22.615 --> 06:25.852
Female Caucasian
about 16 years old.

06:25.918 --> 06:28.054
There appears to be no signs
of violence.

06:28.121 --> 06:30.690
We've notified the judge,
he's on his way here now.

06:32.425 --> 06:34.494
Sir, that's Malena Baldo.

06:34.560 --> 06:35.928
She's one of the three
missing girls.

06:35.995 --> 06:37.230
Block the perimeter.

06:37.330 --> 06:38.998
I want those people
200 feet away.

06:39.065 --> 06:41.534
Excuse me, but I found something
on the body, and I'd like to...

06:41.601 --> 06:43.236
Do you want
this poor girl's parents

06:43.302 --> 06:46.172
to see their dead daughter's
picture on tomorrow's newspaper?

06:46.239 --> 06:48.241
RAMON: Let's go, let's go.
Please.

06:48.307 --> 06:49.942
- And go put on the uniform.
RAMON: You can't be here.

06:50.042 --> 06:53.346
You can't be here.
Careful, careful.

06:53.446 --> 06:54.881
Please, step back.
Step back.

06:54.947 --> 06:57.116
REPORTER ON TV:Our worst
suspicions were confirmed

06:57.183 --> 06:59.685
<i>in the case of the three
Almanzora missing girls.</i>

06:59.752 --> 07:02.155
<i>Earlier this morning
a body was discovered</i>

07:02.255 --> 07:05.825
<i>on the shore of one
of the local beaches.</i>

07:05.925 --> 07:07.527
<i>Police sources
have confirmed</i>

07:07.593 --> 07:10.430
<i>that the victim
is Malena Baldo,</i>

07:10.530 --> 07:12.165
<i>who was only
16 years old.</i>

07:16.869 --> 07:19.806
<i>Very sad news to wake up to
this morning.</i>

07:19.872 --> 07:23.676
<i>We had all hoped to find
the three girls alive.</i>

07:23.743 --> 07:26.479
<i>- Thank you, Marina.</i>
- Surely, Sandra's okay.

07:26.546 --> 07:30.149
REPORTER:According to the
police, it is virtually a fact

07:30.249 --> 07:32.652
that the other two missing girls
<i>are being held hostage...</i>

07:32.718 --> 07:35.288
We have to find Malena
before they do.

07:35.354 --> 07:36.889
Well, there she is.

07:43.196 --> 07:44.263
Malena!

07:46.199 --> 07:47.400
Malena!

07:48.868 --> 07:50.203
Malena!

07:53.673 --> 07:55.641
Sandra!

07:55.708 --> 07:57.710
We have to get out.
We have to get out of here.

07:59.479 --> 08:01.214
We're gonna get caught.
We have to go now.

08:01.280 --> 08:02.815
We have to get out of here.

08:06.786 --> 08:08.855
BEA: If anyone's here,
reveal yourself.

08:16.629 --> 08:18.798
If anyone's here,
give us a sign.

08:22.068 --> 08:23.970
[snickering]

08:24.036 --> 08:26.239
Are you taking this seriously
or not, Olivia?

08:26.305 --> 08:28.107
Actually, no.
And you know why?

08:28.207 --> 08:30.710
Because this is
absolutely stupid, okay, Bea?

08:30.810 --> 08:33.546
Dude, we're not
three years old anymore, okay?

08:33.646 --> 08:35.681
- And I've told you a million...
- It's for Javi.

08:37.583 --> 08:41.554
I feel him around me
all the time.

08:41.654 --> 08:43.789
I sense him like
he's here with me.

08:45.992 --> 08:47.960
And there's one thing
he should know.

08:49.295 --> 08:50.796
It's too important.

08:53.165 --> 08:54.767
[sighs]

08:58.271 --> 09:00.206
[chuckles]

09:01.474 --> 09:02.408
[sighs]

09:02.475 --> 09:05.678
If anyone's here,
give us a sign.

09:07.480 --> 09:09.916
If anyone's here,
reveal yourself.

09:10.016 --> 09:11.918
[wind gusting]

09:13.319 --> 09:15.154
Was that you?

09:15.254 --> 09:17.823
- Read it, Bea.
- "S," "TEP."

09:17.924 --> 09:20.760
"A." "WAY."

09:20.826 --> 09:23.029
[girls shrieking,
glass shattering]

09:33.306 --> 09:36.642
[both panting]

09:36.709 --> 09:38.444
- What the hell was that?
- It's clear, isn't it?

09:38.511 --> 09:40.012
It was them.
It was Javi!

09:40.079 --> 09:41.547
What do you mean?
That's just impossible, Bea.

09:41.647 --> 09:44.450
But Olivia, you were
right there, you saw it.

09:44.517 --> 09:46.919
Bea, get real.
Ghosts don't exist, okay?

09:46.986 --> 09:49.855
But Olivia,
the glass exploded.

09:49.922 --> 09:51.490
It said "Step away,"
how do you explain that?

09:51.557 --> 09:53.993
The wind, the condensation.
Look, how could I know?

09:54.093 --> 09:55.828
No, that's bullshit!

09:55.928 --> 09:58.631
What is it, Olivia?
Why are you trying to deny it?

09:58.731 --> 10:01.367
- Tell me, what's your problem?
- No, Bea, you tell me.

10:01.434 --> 10:02.368
That boy's dead, period.

10:02.435 --> 10:04.670
And you think
it was your fault?

10:04.770 --> 10:07.073
Well, too bad.
There's nothing you can do.

10:10.743 --> 10:11.811
Bea.

10:14.046 --> 10:15.815
[sighs]
Man.

10:17.016 --> 10:18.317
Shit.

10:19.518 --> 10:20.686
[sighs]

10:20.753 --> 10:23.456
AURELIA:<i> My granddaughter</i>
<i>was born today.</i>

10:23.522 --> 10:26.559
<i>I prayed
it would be a boy,</i>

10:26.626 --> 10:28.794
<i>but she was born a girl.</i>

10:28.894 --> 10:31.998
<i>She is cursed, I know.</i>

10:32.064 --> 10:35.568
<i>She'll inherit my gift
and my malediction.</i>

10:44.243 --> 10:45.845
No, it doesn't make any sense.
Why are they

10:45.911 --> 10:47.213
- at the salt flats, huh?
- Almanzora Police Station.

10:47.279 --> 10:48.247
It doesn't make
any sense, Costa.

10:48.314 --> 10:49.749
Stop it, Mario.

10:49.849 --> 10:50.983
I've told you,
we don't answer the press.

10:51.083 --> 10:52.885
- Stop calling.
- Listen to me.

10:52.952 --> 10:54.654
You know it's impossible,
the wind came from the north.

10:54.720 --> 10:55.988
Why would they be in
the salt flats in the south?

10:56.088 --> 10:57.790
I don't know, Mario!
I don't know, okay?

10:57.890 --> 10:59.525
But these people
have experience.

10:59.592 --> 11:00.960
They're trained,
they know what they're doing.

11:01.027 --> 11:02.762
[phone ringing]
Geez!

11:02.828 --> 11:04.563
Almanzora Police Station,
what the hell can I do for you?

11:04.630 --> 11:06.365
Listen, I may not
be trained, okay?

11:06.432 --> 11:08.067
But I do know the ocean.

11:08.167 --> 11:10.236
If the wind comes from
the north, so does the body.

11:10.336 --> 11:12.304
Geez, you're making a mistake.

11:15.107 --> 11:16.308
[sighs]

11:18.244 --> 11:20.079
MALENA: What do they want
to do to us?

11:21.647 --> 11:24.984
Why are they feeding us
these bugs?

11:25.084 --> 11:27.153
[whimpering]

11:28.554 --> 11:30.923
[gasps]

11:30.990 --> 11:33.359
Did you hear that noise?

11:33.426 --> 11:35.961
Footsteps.

11:36.028 --> 11:38.864
- I think they're coming for us.
- This poor girl's

11:38.964 --> 11:40.266
- got a screw loose.
- They're coming.

11:40.366 --> 11:42.802
- For real, right?
- Please stop.

11:42.868 --> 11:45.504
- Yeah.
- No, please, don't.

11:45.604 --> 11:47.373
But she knows
where my sister is.

11:47.440 --> 11:48.908
I can't stand this anymore.

11:49.008 --> 11:51.110
Why don't they just
kill us already?

11:51.210 --> 11:52.945
Hey, hey,
what's he doing?

11:53.045 --> 11:54.447
I don't know.

11:54.513 --> 11:56.015
[sobbing]

11:57.483 --> 11:59.485
Malena.

12:04.557 --> 12:06.492
Sandra?

12:07.693 --> 12:08.961
Yeah.

12:10.262 --> 12:11.630
Yeah, it's me.

12:11.731 --> 12:14.133
♪♪♪

12:30.950 --> 12:33.252
[panting]

12:43.796 --> 12:47.333
I told you we shouldn't
go out for a smoke.

12:47.399 --> 12:48.634
I told you,
I told you that man

12:48.734 --> 12:50.002
was looking at us
in a funny way.

12:50.069 --> 12:51.170
What man?

12:56.442 --> 12:59.879
What is this place?
How did we get here?

12:59.945 --> 13:01.347
Why do they bathe us

13:01.447 --> 13:02.915
with those soaps
and then shave us?

13:03.015 --> 13:05.317
Tell me, why do they
feed us bugs?

13:05.384 --> 13:06.986
What do they want
to do with us?

13:07.086 --> 13:08.254
We'll leave this place,

13:08.320 --> 13:09.488
- I promise.
- You shut up!

13:11.157 --> 13:13.759
You keep repeating that,
but it's not true.

13:13.826 --> 13:15.561
You're not saving us this time.

13:15.628 --> 13:16.996
Can't you see?

13:17.797 --> 13:21.033
We're about to die here.

13:21.133 --> 13:23.235
We're about
to die here, Sandra!

13:25.805 --> 13:27.039
No, Malena, listen to me.

13:27.106 --> 13:31.243
I've got the key.
Do you hear me?

13:31.310 --> 13:33.312
I've got the key.
I've opened the door.

13:33.412 --> 13:34.346
We're out.

13:37.349 --> 13:39.885
We have to get out of here.
Now, run!

13:42.721 --> 13:44.890
- What do we do next?
- I don't know.

13:44.957 --> 13:46.325
All of the corridors look alike.

13:46.392 --> 13:47.693
But maybe there's a door
or a window.

13:47.760 --> 13:48.727
That way!

13:48.794 --> 13:49.962
Run!

13:51.597 --> 13:54.033
What do we do now?

13:54.133 --> 13:54.567
[screaming]

13:54.633 --> 13:55.768
What is it?

13:55.835 --> 13:58.270
- Ah!
- What is it?

13:58.370 --> 13:59.705
- That noise!
- What?

13:59.805 --> 14:01.307
I hate that horrible noise.

14:01.407 --> 14:02.274
- What?
- Turn off that bloody machine,

14:02.374 --> 14:04.210
- Sandra!
- A machine? What noise?

14:04.276 --> 14:06.045
Come on.
They'll catch us.

14:06.111 --> 14:08.280
They're too close.
Run, Sandra!

14:08.347 --> 14:09.849
- Let's-- let's go, run!
- What?

14:09.915 --> 14:11.317
- What is it?
- Too close!

14:11.383 --> 14:13.919
Malena!
Malena, stop!

14:13.986 --> 14:15.688
Stop!
Malena! Come here!

14:15.754 --> 14:18.490
Malena, what noise?

14:19.625 --> 14:22.228
The sound of water.

14:22.328 --> 14:24.597
[sobbing]

14:24.663 --> 14:26.465
The fucking sound of water.

14:26.565 --> 14:28.067
[sobbing]

14:34.673 --> 14:36.041
The water.

14:44.350 --> 14:45.384
The water.

14:48.487 --> 14:49.788
Javi?

14:53.626 --> 14:55.094
I did it.

14:55.160 --> 14:57.363
I jumped
and abandoned them there.

15:02.534 --> 15:04.036
Please forgive me.

15:21.253 --> 15:23.289
[sobbing]

15:26.025 --> 15:28.627
[door unlocking,
keys jingling]

15:49.048 --> 15:51.850
<i>Our worst suspicions
were confirmed</i>

15:51.917 --> 15:54.486
<i>in the case of the three
Almanzora missing girls.</i>

15:54.553 --> 15:57.189
<i>Earlier this morning,
a body was discovered</i>

15:57.289 --> 15:59.491
<i>on the shore of one
of the local beaches.</i>

15:59.558 --> 16:01.760
<i>Police sources have confirmed
that the victim</i>

16:01.827 --> 16:04.263
<i>is Malena Baldo,
who was only 16 years old.</i>

16:04.363 --> 16:08.067
REPORTER 2:Very sad news
to wake up to this morning.

16:08.167 --> 16:09.635
REPORTER:<i> She was</i>
<i>16 years old.</i>

16:09.735 --> 16:11.437
<i>The body of Malena Baldo
was found this morning...</i>

16:11.503 --> 16:13.906
REPORTER 3:<i> The investigators</i>
<i>are considering drowning</i>

16:14.006 --> 16:16.675
<i>as the possible cause of
death of the young Malena
Baldo,</i>

16:16.742 --> 16:18.944
who was found dead this morning
<i>on a beach by Almanzora.</i>

16:19.044 --> 16:21.613
<i>Three young boys
have passed away</i>

16:21.680 --> 16:23.349
and the condition of another boy
<i>is extremely critical</i>

16:23.449 --> 16:26.719
<i>after an accidental fire at
a nightclub on the outskirts</i>

16:26.785 --> 16:28.087
<i>- of their hometown...
- Sandra Merino's brother</i>

16:28.153 --> 16:29.922
<i>- has died.
- ...all between 13</i>

16:29.989 --> 16:30.756
<i>- and 15 years old. - The
death of Sandra Merino's</i>

16:30.856 --> 16:33.425
<i>brother, Javier Merino...</i>

16:33.525 --> 16:35.627
<i>...unwilling to comment on
the causes of this tragedy.</i>

16:35.728 --> 16:39.832
<i>[overlapping chatter]</i>

16:52.811 --> 16:55.147
[knocking, doorbell ringing]

16:59.918 --> 17:02.855
- I got us pastries.
- I'm not hungry.

17:08.293 --> 17:10.229
- Are you really doing this?
- God.

17:10.329 --> 17:13.065
- Doing what, hm?
- Not talking to me.

17:13.165 --> 17:14.767
- I just don't get it.
- What don't you get?

17:14.833 --> 17:16.468
You, Costa!
I don't get you.

17:16.568 --> 17:17.603
What the hell are you doing?

17:17.669 --> 17:19.438
- What I can, Mario.
- That's bullshit.

17:19.505 --> 17:20.839
You're blind shooting,
following absurd leads.

17:20.906 --> 17:23.075
- I mean, it's just stupid.
- Mario, Mario, listen.

17:23.175 --> 17:24.843
- The investigation is botched.
- It is not-- I know that!

17:26.111 --> 17:28.647
But I'm a fucking secretary.

17:28.714 --> 17:30.516
That is the reality.

17:31.483 --> 17:34.319
[sighs]

17:34.386 --> 17:35.054
Hey, no.

17:37.556 --> 17:39.391
You're the only person
that loves them as much as I do.

17:39.491 --> 17:40.759
Look at me.

17:40.826 --> 17:43.829
Sandra only has us two.

17:43.929 --> 17:46.565
Without you, I...

17:46.632 --> 17:49.668
You are not alone.

17:49.768 --> 17:51.036
I swear, you are not alone.

17:52.704 --> 17:54.807
But you have to trust me.

18:07.786 --> 18:11.356
<i>The entire town awoke
heartbroken this morning.</i>

18:11.423 --> 18:13.692
<i>The lifeless body of one
of the Almanzora girls</i>

18:13.759 --> 18:15.327
<i>has been found.</i>

18:15.394 --> 18:18.030
<i>We've interrupted
our scheduled programming</i>

18:18.130 --> 18:19.965
to bring you this special report
<i>from the very heart</i>

18:20.032 --> 18:22.668
<i>- of the story.</i>
- [phone ringing]

18:22.768 --> 18:25.170
<i>Welcome to
"Where Are They?"</i>

18:25.237 --> 18:27.406
- Yes? -<i> "The Almanzora</i>
<i>Special."</i>

18:27.473 --> 18:29.208
Leave me alone, damn it!

18:29.274 --> 18:31.643
[TV playing music]

18:39.518 --> 18:42.454
JAVI: Bea.

18:42.521 --> 18:42.921
Bea.

18:54.233 --> 18:56.635
♪♪♪

19:24.329 --> 19:26.064
[tires screeching]

19:27.633 --> 19:29.568
ROCA: Hang in there, Bea!

19:29.635 --> 19:31.370
Hang in there, sweetie.

19:31.436 --> 19:31.904
Hold on, please.

19:35.641 --> 19:38.043
Come on, princess.

19:42.047 --> 19:43.515
Please, hold on.

19:53.692 --> 19:55.761
Come on, sunshine.

19:55.827 --> 19:58.230
Don't leave me alone, please.

19:58.330 --> 19:59.631
Come on!

20:04.570 --> 20:07.206
Come on, honey.

20:07.272 --> 20:08.440
Bea, please!

20:08.507 --> 20:11.810
[Bea gasping, coughing]

20:12.945 --> 20:13.011
Dad?

20:14.913 --> 20:16.748
- Honey!
- [coughs]

20:17.683 --> 20:19.985
[Roca sobbing]

21:49.107 --> 21:50.409
No!

21:50.475 --> 21:53.245
No! No! No!

22:04.456 --> 22:07.793
[panting]

22:14.166 --> 22:14.933
We're trapped here.

22:30.215 --> 22:32.284
REPORTER:Mr. Merino, I'd like
to ask you a few questions.

22:32.351 --> 22:33.352
<i>Do you think your daughter
is still alive?</i>

22:33.452 --> 22:35.887
<i>Do you think
she's being tortured?</i>

22:39.791 --> 22:40.992
<i>This silence
is the only response</i>

22:41.093 --> 22:43.562
<i>from a man broken
by grief today,</i>

22:43.628 --> 22:47.132
<i>Mario Merino, father of one
of the girls from Almanzora</i>

22:47.199 --> 22:48.333
<i>who is still alive.</i>

22:48.400 --> 22:52.070
<i>A father that is probably
feeling fear,</i>

22:52.170 --> 22:54.906
<i>and pain,
and also some relief,</i>

22:55.006 --> 22:56.708
<i>because after all,
the girl they found</i>

22:56.808 --> 22:59.044
<i>was not his daughter.</i>

22:59.111 --> 23:01.480
REPORTER 2:We've just seen
Mario Merino.

23:01.546 --> 23:03.849
<i>He had little to say.
He's a father</i>

23:03.915 --> 23:06.985
<i>who refuses to give up
his desperate search</i>

23:07.085 --> 23:08.920
<i>for his daughter.</i>

23:08.987 --> 23:12.190
<i>For him, today's news, the
discovery of Malena's body</i>

23:12.290 --> 23:14.826
<i>is actually not
very encouraging.</i>

23:14.926 --> 23:19.231
<i>But at least the victim's
body is not his daughter's.</i>

23:19.331 --> 23:21.600
<i>We must remember that this
is not the first tragedy</i>

23:21.666 --> 23:23.135
<i>to strike the
Merino family.</i>

24:02.274 --> 24:05.243
MAN: We have to also consider
all these factors

24:05.310 --> 24:08.847
for us to be able to proceed
with the investigation.

24:08.914 --> 24:11.583
The girl's report.
Fax it to the judge.

24:11.683 --> 24:12.984
Okay.

24:13.084 --> 24:15.120
MARIANO: Selma,
there's a report missing, okay?

24:15.187 --> 24:17.055
It should be here pretty soon.
I already sent the request,

24:17.122 --> 24:18.323
but we need to update
the documentation.

24:18.390 --> 24:21.426
Please let me know
so we can update it in time

24:21.526 --> 24:23.562
and we don't have to send
another request again.

24:23.628 --> 24:25.864
Mariano.

24:25.964 --> 24:28.967
- And the bugs?
- What?

24:29.034 --> 24:30.268
Nothing.

24:48.553 --> 24:50.655
ZETA: It was like being
a fucking hamster

24:50.722 --> 24:52.891
- inside a goddamn wheel.
- A classic.

24:52.958 --> 24:54.926
Ghosts can't leave the place
where they're buried.

24:54.993 --> 24:56.228
It's like in "Poltergeist."

24:56.328 --> 24:57.796
Or like in "Sleepy Hollow."

24:57.896 --> 24:59.764
Every time the Horseman
tries to cross the bridge,

24:59.831 --> 25:00.999
- a force stops him.
- Mm-hmm.

25:01.066 --> 25:01.933
But there has to be a way
to get into the dam.

25:02.000 --> 25:04.169
They need
to get out of there.

25:04.236 --> 25:05.871
We get there, and then what?

25:05.971 --> 25:08.406
You know we can't touch anything
or punch anyone.

25:14.246 --> 25:15.413
What am I missing?

25:19.451 --> 25:23.355
Yesterday, I ran into Olivia,
and it seemed like she heard me.

25:23.455 --> 25:25.991
- What?!
- We're not speaking to her.

25:26.091 --> 25:27.792
- Why not?
- Can she talk to dead people?

25:27.893 --> 25:29.427
We don't know for sure.
Quino just thought she did.

25:29.528 --> 25:30.996
- Let's go see what happens.
- No!

25:31.062 --> 25:32.764
I promised her grandma
we'd keep her out of this.

25:32.831 --> 25:34.733
I don't care what
you promised her.

25:34.799 --> 25:36.368
Our necks are on
the line too, man.

25:36.434 --> 25:38.870
What about us?
Risking going to the Abyss?

25:38.970 --> 25:40.672
And besides,
it's not your decision.

25:42.107 --> 25:45.510
The Mortise was murdered
for helping us.

25:45.610 --> 25:49.948
Do you wanna risk the same thing
happening to Olivia?

25:50.048 --> 25:53.752
I don't know, but it's
your sister who's a hostage.

25:53.852 --> 25:55.954
She's locked up
and can't get out.

26:12.470 --> 26:14.039
This is fucking great.

26:36.628 --> 26:38.930
[knocking]

26:38.997 --> 26:40.131
Yes?

26:42.667 --> 26:44.169
- Hey.
- Hi.

26:47.272 --> 26:50.175
I spoke to the doctor.
You should rest until tomorrow.

26:50.241 --> 26:51.343
Fine.

26:57.015 --> 26:58.483
Why do you hate them so much?

26:58.550 --> 27:00.452
Javi?
His father?

27:00.518 --> 27:01.987
What did they do to you?

27:02.087 --> 27:03.722
We're not talking
about that now.

27:03.788 --> 27:05.957
You were friends.

27:06.024 --> 27:08.159
So was my mother.

27:08.226 --> 27:09.427
What happened?

27:10.929 --> 27:13.164
I don't wanna talk about it.

27:13.231 --> 27:15.000
Well, I do.

27:15.066 --> 27:18.036
I'm not a little girl anymore.

27:18.103 --> 27:19.904
Please, tell me.
Tell me everything.

27:20.005 --> 27:21.473
What happened to you?

27:38.623 --> 27:40.425
[door closes]

28:00.879 --> 28:04.015
MAN ON TV:First,
the three girls disappeared

28:04.082 --> 28:06.251
<i>from the grounds
of the Paraiso nightclub</i>

28:06.317 --> 28:07.652
<i>during the Full
Moon Party,</i>

28:07.719 --> 28:10.155
one of the biggest celebrations
<i>in the community.</i>

28:12.323 --> 28:14.893
<i>The police department is
still searching for leads</i>

28:14.959 --> 28:16.628
<i>and talking to the locals</i>

28:16.728 --> 28:17.962
<i>in the hope of receiving
some clues</i>

28:18.029 --> 28:21.366
<i>that will lead them
to the girls' whereabouts.</i>

28:21.433 --> 28:24.035
<i>However, so far, no one
remembers seeing them leave</i>

28:24.102 --> 28:27.372
or even seeing them on the road.

28:27.439 --> 28:28.640
<i>And for those of you
who are just...</i>

28:28.707 --> 28:29.040
Come on, mark the dam.

28:32.477 --> 28:33.511
That's it.

28:34.879 --> 28:36.147
Well done!

28:36.247 --> 28:38.149
Please, go on.

28:38.249 --> 28:39.984
- You'll find them now.
<i>- We bring you</i>

28:40.085 --> 28:41.686
<i>an exclusive
breaking story.</i>

28:41.753 --> 28:43.755
<i>However, we must warn you,
this may be shocking</i>

28:43.855 --> 28:45.156
<i>to some viewers.</i>

28:45.223 --> 28:48.960
SANDRA:Hello.
I'm Sandra Merino.

28:49.027 --> 28:51.029
I was kidnapped three months ago
<i>in Almanzora.</i>

28:53.565 --> 28:56.968
<i>I speak on behalf
of Eva too.</i>

28:57.035 --> 28:59.804
<i>We wanna send a message
to our families.</i>

28:59.871 --> 29:02.373
<i>To be honest, we can't
believe what the network</i>

29:02.440 --> 29:04.175
<i>has just received,
we're shocked.</i>

29:04.242 --> 29:05.877
<i>It's the preview
of a message</i>

29:05.944 --> 29:08.680
<i>recorded by
the kidnappers themselves.</i>

29:08.747 --> 29:11.316
What we just heard is the voice
<i>of Sandra Merino,</i>

29:11.416 --> 29:13.118
<i>ladies and gentlemen.</i>

29:13.184 --> 29:15.987
<i>I've been informed that
this is just a fragment</i>

29:16.087 --> 29:19.324
of a message that the kidnappers
<i>will broadcast</i>

29:19.390 --> 29:22.994
<i>through this network
this evening at 8:30 p.m.</i>

29:23.094 --> 29:25.764
<i>A shocking twist
that has arisen in a case</i>

29:25.830 --> 29:27.999
<i>that has touched
all of us.</i>

29:28.066 --> 29:29.267
<i>- We are in Almanzora...</i>
- Come on, don't give up.

29:29.367 --> 29:30.969
<i>...we are at the heart
of the news...</i>

29:31.035 --> 29:34.105
Come on, please,
they're at the dam.

29:34.205 --> 29:35.573
Please, don't give up!

29:38.910 --> 29:41.279
[ghostly whispering]

29:56.961 --> 29:58.930
[low distorted voices]

30:08.706 --> 30:11.442
[voices continue]

30:33.765 --> 30:36.167
AURELIA: [voice distorted]

30:36.234 --> 30:39.237
<i>She'll inherit my gift
and my malediction.</i>

30:40.672 --> 30:43.074
QUINO: Holy shit,
I can't believe it.

30:43.174 --> 30:44.042
OLIVIA: Who the hell are you?

30:50.915 --> 30:51.916
Quino?

30:53.852 --> 30:55.787
Can you see me?

31:01.226 --> 31:02.760
<i>For those of you
joining us now,</i>

31:02.827 --> 31:05.964
<i>there's a breakthrough
in the case we're covering.</i>

31:06.030 --> 31:08.600
<i>This network has received
an exclusive,</i>

31:08.666 --> 31:11.169
<i>a fragment of a message
with the voice</i>

31:11.236 --> 31:13.238
<i>of one of the
missing girls.</i>

31:13.304 --> 31:17.208
<i>At 8:30 p.m., you will be
able to listen to the full
message.</i>

31:17.275 --> 31:18.743
Those motherfuckers.

31:18.843 --> 31:21.279
<i>It was at this nightclub,
Paraiso,</i>

31:21.346 --> 31:25.783
<i>where Sandra Merino's brother
died in a tragic fire</i>

31:25.884 --> 31:29.654
<i>a few weeks after
his sister's disappearance.</i>

31:29.721 --> 31:32.023
<i>But what really defines
this case...</i>

31:32.123 --> 31:33.892
- [thud]
<i>- ...is mostly the number</i>

31:33.958 --> 31:36.227
<i>of questions
that it raises.</i>

31:36.327 --> 31:38.162
<i>During the Full
Moon Party,</i>

31:38.229 --> 31:40.331
<i>one of the most important
celebrations</i>

31:40.398 --> 31:42.600
<i>for the Almanzora
community...</i>

31:42.667 --> 31:44.969
[muffled chatter]

32:00.919 --> 32:02.086
JAVI: Dad.

32:05.823 --> 32:07.191
Javi?

32:08.593 --> 32:10.762
[rustling]

32:53.604 --> 32:56.040
[music box playing]

33:26.804 --> 33:30.008
BEA: How did she die?
ISIDRO: They didn't tell you?

33:30.074 --> 33:32.143
BEA: I know it was an accident,
but my father

33:32.243 --> 33:33.945
resists to talk
about that topic.

33:35.446 --> 33:38.883
ISIDRO: It was very sad.
Two young women,

33:38.950 --> 33:39.951
such good friends.

33:42.587 --> 33:44.956
It's a coincidence they died
on the same day.

33:46.624 --> 33:47.825
BEA: Who were?

33:49.560 --> 33:50.928
ISIDRO: Javi Merino's mother.

33:57.368 --> 33:59.771
♪♪♪

36:01.425 --> 36:02.760
Please, come on.

36:02.827 --> 36:04.629
Come on. Come on.

36:04.729 --> 36:05.963
[electrical zapping,
Javi gasps]

36:14.572 --> 36:14.906
Damn it.

36:38.563 --> 36:40.932
[nut cracking]

36:43.534 --> 36:45.403
The Marquis is angry.

36:45.469 --> 36:49.040
There have been
a lot of mistakes.

36:49.106 --> 36:49.173
Too many.

36:52.443 --> 36:53.678
Would you like one?

36:57.949 --> 37:00.318
There's an explanation
for all of this.

37:02.787 --> 37:04.388
The prophecy's true.

37:04.488 --> 37:05.990
It's impossible.

37:11.662 --> 37:12.964
Get everything ready.
We're moving them.

37:15.533 --> 37:16.067
Zhou.

37:17.935 --> 37:22.273
We need to find
another girl.

37:43.728 --> 37:46.330
[people chattering]

37:53.204 --> 37:54.372
REPORTER:In just a few
more minutes, we'll listen

37:54.438 --> 37:58.109
<i>to Sandra Merino
and Eva Peñon's message.</i>

37:58.209 --> 37:59.210
<i>What do the kidnappers
wanna tell us</i>

37:59.277 --> 38:02.680
<i>through these
two poor teenagers?</i>

38:02.747 --> 38:04.915
<i>We will soon find out.</i>

38:05.016 --> 38:06.984
OLIVIA: Wait, Quino!
Don't leave me here

38:07.084 --> 38:08.686
- talking to myself.
- I shouldn't be talking to you.

38:08.753 --> 38:09.954
I'm putting you in danger.
What the hell did I do?

38:10.054 --> 38:11.989
You should have thought of that
way before doing

38:12.089 --> 38:13.524
your Ouija exhibition.

38:16.193 --> 38:21.232
- What exhibition?
- The Paraiso thing.

38:21.332 --> 38:24.568
The glass explosion
and all that "step away" crap.

38:26.070 --> 38:27.772
No, no, it wasn't us.

38:30.007 --> 38:31.676
Then who?

38:31.776 --> 38:33.678
- [sighs]
- Who was it?

38:54.031 --> 38:55.333
<i>All right, now we have it.
We have the full recording</i>

38:55.399 --> 38:59.837
<i>of the two Almanzora girls,
Sandra and Eva.</i>

38:59.904 --> 39:02.306
<i>They are two
ordinary girls,</i>

39:02.406 --> 39:05.376
<i>two young kids who were in
the prime of their lives.</i>

39:08.012 --> 39:10.314
<i>♪♪♪</i>

39:25.963 --> 39:28.332
<i>At this point,
we wanna warn our viewers</i>

39:28.399 --> 39:29.967
<i>that the message
we are about to hear is,</i>

39:30.034 --> 39:32.570
<i>to say the
least, upsetting.</i>

39:32.636 --> 39:33.971
<i>Let's listen.</i>

39:37.007 --> 39:39.210
SANDRA:<i> Hello.</i>

39:39.276 --> 39:39.944
<i>I'm Sandra Merino.</i>

39:42.346 --> 39:46.283
I was kidnapped three months ago
<i>in Almanzora.</i>

39:47.718 --> 39:49.553
<i>I speak on behalf
of Eva too.</i>

39:51.789 --> 39:53.724
<i>We wanna send--
we wanna send a message</i>

39:53.791 --> 39:55.726
<i>to our-- to our families.</i>

39:58.763 --> 40:01.031
<i>They've asked to tell you
please not to worry.</i>

40:07.405 --> 40:09.507
<i>We are both fine.</i>

40:11.776 --> 40:16.313
<i>They feed us, and we sleepin
a nice and comfortable
place.</i>

40:31.896 --> 40:32.863
Sandra.

40:34.265 --> 40:35.366
Sandra!

40:36.333 --> 40:37.635
Sandra!

40:37.735 --> 40:39.370
SANDRA:They treat us
with respect.

40:41.205 --> 40:42.573
<i>They're not hurting us.</i>

40:46.310 --> 40:50.681
<i>They say that what happened
to Malena was an accident.</i>

40:52.450 --> 40:54.118
<i>They are not murderers.</i>

40:54.185 --> 40:55.920
<i>They never wanted that
to happen.</i>

41:03.294 --> 41:07.965
<i>Shortly, you'll receive
instructions about what to
do.</i>

41:08.032 --> 41:09.033
JAVI: Sandra! SANDRA:<i> They</i>
<i>say that if we</i>

41:09.133 --> 41:11.502
<i>- listen to them...</i>
- Sandra!

41:11.602 --> 41:12.102
<i>...we get out
of this alive.</i>

41:12.203 --> 41:15.673
Sandra! Sandra!

41:17.174 --> 41:18.476
<i>If we don't...</i>

41:20.478 --> 41:23.214
<i>they'll kill us.
[sobbing]</i>

41:25.115 --> 41:27.451
[people murmuring]

41:44.034 --> 41:45.169
[gasps]

41:51.275 --> 41:53.544
They're here.
Where's Malena?

41:57.248 --> 41:58.182
[gasping]

42:00.284 --> 42:03.053
Malena! Malena!

42:04.588 --> 42:07.224
It was your stepfather.
He kidnapped us!

42:07.992 --> 42:09.994
- No!
- Now run!

42:10.094 --> 42:12.062
- No!
- Run!

42:13.664 --> 42:15.633
[screaming]

42:48.999 --> 42:51.335
[door opens,
keys jingling]

44:33.804 --> 44:36.707
Uh... yes, sir?

44:36.807 --> 44:38.442
A lot of work?

44:38.509 --> 44:40.644
Well, yeah.
Old cases.

44:42.680 --> 44:45.315
Your father told me
you're taking a few days off.

44:45.416 --> 44:48.285
- Mm-hmm.
- I hope it's nothing serious.

44:48.352 --> 44:51.288
Mm, no.
Personal affairs.

44:57.928 --> 44:59.430
Don't leave too late.

45:19.283 --> 45:21.318
BEA: Hey! Hey, wait!

45:53.584 --> 45:55.552
[window whirring]

45:57.855 --> 46:00.824
Hello.
I'm on my way to Villajoyosa,

46:00.924 --> 46:02.359
to the old spa.
Do you know it?

46:02.426 --> 46:04.962
DOLORES: Of course I do.
Hop in, sweetheart.

46:20.344 --> 46:22.079
Thank God you stopped for me.

46:22.146 --> 46:24.314
Otherwise I was in
for a long walk.

46:24.414 --> 46:26.517
Yes, you were very lucky.

46:26.583 --> 46:27.985
Thank you.

46:32.589 --> 46:34.992
♪♪♪
